snippet.title: Amber Heard interviewed at the LA Premiere Screening of #LondonFields #NowPlaying
snippet.description:
https://www.redcarpetreporttv.com

RCRs @FionaZaring talks to @realamberheard at #LondonFields Movie Premiere #NowPlaying #WeAskMore

Mingle Media TV and Red Carpet Report host, Fiona Zaring were at LA Premiere Screening of London Fields at the London Hotel in Hollywood and spoke with cast members about this new film.

London Fields Is In Theaters October 26, 2018

For video interviews and other Red Carpet Report coverage, please visit http://www.redcarpetreporttv.com and follow us on Twitter and Facebook at:
http://twitter.com/TheRedCarpetTV
https://www.facebook.com/RedCarpetReport
http://www.youtube.com/MingleMediaTVNetwork
AboutLondon Fields
Martin Amis' 1989 novel “London Fields” was set in a then-futuristic 1999 and painted a portrait of a world plagued by an unnamed Crisis, where men behave badly and a woman, Nicola Six (Amber Heard), waits for her birthday, when she plans to be murdered.

Directed by: Mathew Cullen 
Starring: Billy Bob Thornton, Amber Heard, Jim Sturgess, Theo James, Cara Delevingne, Gemma Chan andJason Isaacs
Produced by: Chris Hanley and Jordan Gertner
Co-Written by: Roberta Hanley and Martin Amis
Based on the novel by: Martin Amis
